    <statement>
        <p>
            Given the vector equation <m>\hat{ r }(t)=\langle -2 \, t + 1, \frac{5}{2} \, t + 5 \rangle</m>:
            
            <ol>
                <li>Write this equation as parametric equations .</li>
                <li>Sketch the graph of the corresponding curve.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
            <m>x(t)=-2 \, t + 1, y(t)=\frac{5}{2} \, t + 5</m>.
    </answer>
</exercise>
